By Andile Mngxitama When the African National Congress (ANC) issued instructions that its members must not support President Zuma, we as Black First Land First (BLF) stood firmly with him. We pointed out that KPMG is a criminal organization that concocted the 783 charges against President Zuma to deflect attention from the mass murderer FW De Klerk who was supposed to be arrested and prosecuted instead; and to subvert the program of radical economic transformation (RET) that Zuma symbolizes. We said to KPMG, since you have withdrawn your report on the criminal activities of Pravin Gordhan regarding the Rogue Unit at SARS, also withdraw your report upon which you formulated false charges against Zuma. History has no blank pages. Let the record show. This YouTube video (see link) is instructive: https://youtu.be/USzd2i_GIJY Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF), a radical black consciousness organization.